 cultural ownership of an indigenous plant. This heritage-based struggle over rooibos shows how communities negotiate landscapes marked by racial dispossession within an ecosystem imperiled by climate change and precarious social relations in the postapartheid era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Sep 2020) 0aRooibos tea industryxSouth Africa. 0aRooibos tea industryzSouth Africa. 0aRooibos teaxSouth Africa. 0aRooibos teazSouth Africa. 0aRooibos tea. 70(DE-588)4009193-40(DE-627)1045781730(DE-576)208881018aSangVolk2gnd 70(DE-588)4025936-50(DE-627)1045642880(DE-576)208963847aKhoikhoin2gnd 70(DE-588)4033542-20(DE-627)10625670X0(DE-576)20900259XaKulturelle Identität2gnd 70(DE-588)4047353-30(DE-627)10619481X0(DE-576)209073306aProduktionsfaktor2gnd 70(DE-588)4047363-60(DE-627)1044191130(DE-576)209073365aProduktionsgenossenschaft2gnd 70(DE-588)4059283-20(DE-627)1046970670(DE-576)209130237aTee2gnd 70(DE-588)4063790-60(DE-627)1041066030(DE-576)209150475aVolk2gnd 70(DE-588)4123525-30(DE-627)1057545280(DE-576)209560479aKleinbauer2gnd 70(DE-588)4130642-90(DE-627)1057010410(DE-576)209620706aLebensbedingungen2gnd 70(DE-588)4138634-60(DE-627)1056412270(DE-576)20968772XaStammgEthnologie2gnd 70(DE-588)4174079-80(DE-627)1046960520(DE-576)20995471XaPflanzliches Produkt2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2017z978311069634940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822372301zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822372301423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822372301.jpg  a978-3-11-069634-9  DUK eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles